The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Assault after conversion slur

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Bhubaneswar, Dec. 21: Three men and a tribal woman in a village of Balasore district were allegedly assaulted by the brother of a BJP legislator and his supporters on suspicion that they were promoting conversion.

 The incident happened when five people were holding a prayer meeting in Shantilata Sing?s house at Gopinath village on Sunday evening.

 A crowd of over 20 people, mostly supporters of the Sangh Parivar, attacked the men, said the FIR lodged by Shantilata.

 Dhanura Hansda, Sanjay Pal and Dubai Tudu were allegedly beaten up by a group led by Kishor Sarangi, brother of Nilagiri BJP MLA Pratap Sarangi, . 

 In another FIR lodged with the police the same day, Geda Singh, a villager, alleged that he was beaten up by minority community members as he refused to change his faith. 

 The police have started investigations.

 Armed police forces have been deployed in the village. A memorandum was submitted by the Bajrang Dal and BJP supporters to the sub-collector of Nilagiri demanding immediate intervention of the administration to curb the ?spread of illegal conversion?.

 The situation in the village was tense but under control, the police said. 




